.TH erl_scan 3 "stdlib 7.3" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
erl_scan \- The Erlang token scanner.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This module contains functions for tokenizing (scanning) characters into Erlang tokens.

.PP
\fBError Information\fR

.PP
\fIErrorInfo\fR is the standard \fIErrorInfo\fR structure that is returned from all I/O modules. The format is as follows:

.IP
.nf
{ErrorLocation, Module, ErrorDescriptor}

.fi

.PP
A string describing the error is obtained with the following call:

.IP
.nf
Module:format_error(ErrorDescriptor)

.fi

.PP
\fBNotes\fR

.PP
The continuation of the first call to the re-entrant input functions must be \fI[]\fR. For a complete description of how the re-entrant input scheme works, see Armstrong, Virding and Williams: 'Concurrent Programming in Erlang', Chapter 13.

.PP
\fBSee Also\fR

.PP
\fIerl_anno\fR, \fIerl_parse\fR, \fIio\fR

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBcategory() :: atom().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBchar_spec() :: string() | eof.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBerror_description() :: term().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBerror_info() ::\fR
\fB          {erl_anno:location(), module(), error_description()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBoption() ::\fR
\fB          return | return_white_spaces | return_comments | text |\fR
\fB          {reserved_word_fun, resword_fun()} |\fR
\fB          {text_fun, text_fun()} |\fR
\fB          {compiler_internal, [term()]}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBoptions() :: option() | [option()].\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBresword_fun() :: fun((atom()) -> boolean()).\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fB-opaque return_cont() \fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBsymbol() :: atom() | float() | integer() | string().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtext_fun() :: fun((atom(), string()) -> boolean()).\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtoken() ::\fR
\fB          {category(), Anno :: erl_anno:anno(), symbol()} |\fR
\fB          {category(), Anno :: erl_anno:anno()}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtokens() :: [token()].\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBtokens_result() ::\fR
\fB          {ok, Tokens :: tokens(), EndLocation :: erl_anno:location()} |\fR
\fB          {eof, EndLocation :: erl_anno:location()} |\fR
